args:
The party arrives at the summit of the mountain.
Following Gatov's instructions, Notte prays at a
lake in order to open the way to the Faerie
Kingdom, but it doesn't work. As they try to
determine what went wrong, a maddened
white-wolf dragon appears and attacks!
I think so! But dude, this whole walking\nthing takes a lot of noodling to do right.\nHow do you guys even deal with legs?
Can't ya just fly around? Yer wings grew\njust as big as the rest'a ya.
Well sure I could, but I wanna learn\nhow to work these things.
I mean, it's a little tricky, but being able to\nwalk like all you guys do is gonna be RAD!
Heck, maybe I can even pull my weight a\nlittle more around this joint now.
Before, I was so small that I just sorta\nflitted around behind you and hoped\neverything worked out, you know?
That's not true at all! You've helped us\nout of any number of sticky situations.
His Highness is correct. Your bright and\ncheerful disposition has ever lifted us up,\neven in the darkest of times.
Yeah, there ain't nothing wrong with being\ntiny so long as your heart's big!
That being said, your present form is\nequally lovely. Those wings are stunning.
Yep. Big or small, you're always\ngoing to be our Notte.
So don't worry about it, all right?
Aw, man! You guys are totally gonna\nmake me ugly cry. *sniff*
Right then, I'm gonna help everyone out\nby leading you to the peak! C'mon!
We seem to have reached the summit.\nGoodness, look at the size of that lake!
Strange. All the snow is melted here.
I bet the faeries are behind that, too.\nIt's spooky how a bunch'a little guys\ncan control the weather and junk.
So the entrance to their kingdom\nis somewhere around here?
Actually, we are standing atop it.\nMuch like the forest, it is hidden\nso as to ward off intruders.
Can Sheila make this entrance appear\nas she did the one earlier?
I'm afraid only a faerie can open the way\nto their own kingdom.
Which means it is up to you, Notte.

Indeed. Now turn and face the lake
while praying as hard as you can. Let
your heart fill with a desire to enter
the Faerie Kingdom.
If your wish rings true, the way to\nthe kingdom will appear before us.
Sounds nutty, but I'll give it a go!
Okay, I'll try not to get in my own\nhead here. Lemme see...
(Uh, hey there, Faerie Kingdom! It's Notte.\nI really, really, REALLY wanna get in there,\nso can ya maybe let me in? ...Please?)
This is most peculiar. The way to the\nkingdom should always open for a faerie.
Oh man, maybe I'm not strong enough.\nOr maybe I'm not faerie-y enough now\nthat I'm so honkin' big!
This isn't your fault, Notte. There must be\nsome other reason it's not working.
Why don't you try it again?
Good idea. This time I'll nail it!
It's a white-wolf dragon!\nBut what is it doing here?
There shouldn't be such dragons\nin this region...
Be careful—the mana coming from this\nbeast has a savage, maddened air.\nI fear the poor creature has lost its mind.
Well, that's a piece'a bad news.\nLooks like we got a fight on our hands!
I don't want to engage a creature that has\nlost its senses, but we don't have a choice!
